SIMPLE: pinchers
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pinchers
<hw>Pinch"ers</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Pinch</er>.]</ety> <def>An instrument having two handles and two
grasping jaws working on a pivot; -- used for griping things to be held
fast, drawing nails, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This spelling is preferable to <xex>pincers</xex>, both
on account of its derivation from the English <xex>pinch</xex>, and
because it represents the common pronunciation.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinchfist</ent>⟦br⟧
